    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Okay, I got it down to asymmetrical handling of the literal.\r\n\r\nWhen the variable is on the left, the compiler checks `IntegerType::binaryOperatorResult`. Inside this call, `commonType` finds that the literal's `RationalNumberType` is implicitly convertible to `int8`'s `IntegerType` However, in `RationalNumberType::binaryOperatorResult`, it first converts itself to its `mobileType`, `uint8`, then checks the operator based on that. Of course, `commonType` finds that `int8` is not implicitly convertible to `uint8`, or vice-versa. Typechecking therefore fails.",
